      <memberdef kind="function" id="classSetGet2_1accffbb26b62b3ebeecb18785000578f0" prot="public" static="yes" const="no" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>bool</type>
        <definition>static bool SetGet2&lt; A1, A2 &gt;::setVec</definition>
        <argsstring>(Id destId, const string &amp;field, const vector&lt; A1 &gt; &amp;arg1, const vector&lt; A2 &gt; &amp;arg2)</argsstring>
        <name>setVec</name>
        <qualifiedname>SetGet2::setVec</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="classId" kindref="compound">Id</ref></type>
          <declname>destId</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const string &amp;</type>
          <declname>field</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const vector&lt; A1 &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>arg1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const vector&lt; A2 &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>arg2</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Assign a vector of targets, using matching vectors of arguments arg1 and arg2. Specifically, index i on the target receives arguments arg1[i], arg2[i]. Note that there is no requirement for the size of the argument vectors to be equal to the size of the target array of objects. If there are fewer arguments then the index cycles back, so as to tile the target array with as many arguments as we have.</para>
<para>Not yet implemented correct handling for FieldElements. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
